7 SECTION 73. A new section of the Severance Tax Bonding
8 Act is enacted to read:
9 "SUPPLEMENTAL SEVERANCE TAX BONDS--UNIVERSITY OF
10 NEW MEXICO SCHOOL OF MEDICINE.--
11 A. The state board of finance shall issue and sell
12 supplemental severance tax bonds in an amount not exceeding a
13 total of two hundred eighty million dollars ($280,000,000) in
14 fiscal years 2026 through 2029 when the board of regents of
15 the university of New Mexico certifies the need for the
16 issuance of bonds to plan, design, construct, equip, furnish
and landscape a new school of medicine; provided that the
17
total issuance of supplemental severance tax bonds in fiscal
18
years 2026 through 2029 shall not exceed the debt service
19
limitations provided for in Subsection D of Section 7-27-14
20
NMSA 1978. The proceeds from the sales of the bonds are
21
appropriated to the board of regents of the university of
22
New Mexico for the purposes enumerated in this subsection.
23
B. The state board of finance shall schedule the
24
issuance and sale of the bonds in the most expeditious and
25 SFC/SB 240
Page 242

1 economical manner possible upon a finding of the board that
2 the project has been developed sufficiently to justify the
3 issuance and that the project can proceed to contract and
4 completion within a reasonable time. The state board of
5 finance shall further take appropriate steps necessary to
6 comply with the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as
7 applicable."
8 SECTION 74. Section 7-27-12 NMSA 1978 (being Laws 1961,
